                           Sotheby's via Bloomberg 
                         
                         "Concetto Spaziale, La Fine di Dio" by artist Lucio Fontana. The work was estimated at 4.5 million pounds to 5.5 million pounds at Sotheby's June 28 auction of contemporary art in London. The oval canvas last appeared on the auction market in February 2001, when it sold for 465,750 pounds. This time it made 4.7 million pounds. 
                       
                     
                                        
           
                     "Concetto Spaziale, La Fine di Dio" by artist Lucio Fontana. The work was estimated at 4.5 million pounds to 5.5 million pounds at Sotheby's June 28 auction of contemporary art in London. The oval canvas last appeared on the auction market in February 2001, when it sold for 465,750 pounds. This time it made 4.7 million pounds. Source: Sotheby's via Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     "Neger (Nuba)" by artist Gerhard Richter. The work was estimated at 3.5 million pounds to 4.5 million pounds in Sotheby's June 28 auction of contemporary art in London. The composition, based on a found photograph of members of the Nuba tribe from Sudan, sold for 3.7 million pounds. Source: Sotheby's via Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                                                 
                     
