                       "RE 49, Relief Eponge Bleu"  
                       
                         
                           Sotheby's via Bloomberg 
                         
                         The 1961 Yves Klein sponge relief, "RE 49, Relief Eponge Bleu," was estimated at 4.5 million pounds to 6.5 million pounds at Sotheby's June 28 auction of contemporary art in London.  The work, entered from the collection of HVB Group, the German banking unit of UniCredit SpA, was bought by one of three telephone bidders for 6.2 million pounds. 
                       
                     
                                        
           
                     The 1961 Yves Klein sponge relief, "RE 49, Relief Eponge Bleu," was estimated at 4.5 million pounds to 6.5 million pounds at Sotheby's June 28 auction of contemporary art in London.  The work, entered from the collection of HVB Group, the German banking unit of UniCredit SpA, was bought by one of three telephone bidders for 6.2 million pounds. Source: Sotheby's via Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     The trio of Andy Warhol silkscreen paintings, "Three Jackies." offered in Sotheby's June 28 sale of contemporary art. Dating from 1964 and never offered at auction before, they were estimated to fetch between 1.5 million pounds and 2 million pounds. The selling price was on the low estimate of 1.5 million pounds. Source: Sotheby's via Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     "Phoenix (Peace Eagle),'' by Matthew Day Jackson. Day Jackson, The work was expected to fetch between 200,000 pounds and 300,000 pounds at Christie's International's June 30 auction of contemporary art in London. It sold for 301,250 pounds with fees. Source: Christie's via Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                                                 
                     
